Nigeria’s first son, Yusuf Buhari has returned to Abuja after spending weeks in Germany receiving medical treatment. It was learnt that Yusuf received treatment at the St. Joseph Hospital in Wiesbaden as well as further treatment to fix a broken arm at another hospital in Munich.
Before leaving Nigeria for Germany on January 12, 2018, Yusuf spent some time at Cedarest Hospital in Abuja after he was injured in a power bike accident in Gwanripa neighborhood in Abuja while drag racing with a friend, Bashir Gwandu. 